{
  "text": "Insulin resistance has also been suggested as a potential risk factor for the development of respiratory problems, such as asthma, in severe obese children and adolescents. In fact, obese children with asthma have a higher degree of insulin resistance than obese children without this respiratory problem, and the state of inflammation associated with insulin resistance has been suggested as a possible mediator of this relationship [CITATION_1] .",
